txt.en: Sâd-en-Dagor, the training-grounds of Dol Guldur, are overseen by three champions of the Lieutenant of Dol Guldur.

'Greetings, [placeholder]. We have much to discuss. Our forces have encountered three champions of Dol Guldur: a sorcerer named Urcheron, the morroval-queen Carchrien, and the Gorthorog war-leader Durkâr. Dread follows in their wake...they must be dealt with, lest our hearts quail and our strength wavers.

'Deep within the fortress of Dol Guldur is a sword-hall, which our scouts believe to be the training-grounds for the warriors of Dol Guldur. If this is so, Urcheron, Carchrien, and Durkâr will surely be near at hand.

'Enter Sâd-en-Dagor and slay these three champions.'
Urcheron, Carchrien, and Durkâr in Sâd-en-Dagor in Dol Guldur, north-east of Helethir.\n\nTorist has asked you to slay Urcheron, Carchrien, and Durkâr, three champions of Dol Guldur.
'You have done it! Fine work, [placeholder]! These warriors posed a great threat to us, but no more.'
Torist is at Helethir, south-west from Dol Guldur.\n\nYou should return to Torist for your reward.
'These are mighty warriors you will be facing...do not underestimate their strength!'
